div.h3: Step 1 - Get task from Azure Board

div.style: text-align: left

ul.li: Find the PBI you want to work on.
Find/create required Task within PBI.
Assign Task to yourself.

div.h3: Step 2 - Create Feature Branch in GitHub and Clone Locally

div.style: text-align: left

ul.li: In GitHub, create feature branch from develop.
Name your branch either:
Replace xxxxx with the PBI number from Step 1.
Replace pbi-description with a description of the PBI.
This naming format is to accommodate our GitHook.
E.g. feature/AB#12345-add-translated-text
Clone feature branch locally.

div.h3: Step 3 - Modify Code to Satisfy Task

ul.li: You may use the tool of your choice.
Dev team primarily uses Visual Studio 2019 Enterprise.

div.h3: Step 4 - Commit changes and Push to GitHub

ul.li: Format for commit messages:
Replace xxxxx with the Task number from Step 1.
Replace commit-message with commit message text.
AB#xxxxx will automatically link this commit in Azure Board.
E.g. AB#23456 Update French text on home page
Push local commits to GitHub.

div.h3: Step 5 - Initiate Pull Request from Feature Branch into develop Branch

div.style: text-align: left

ul.li: Branch protection rules on develop must be satisfied, including:
Code changes must be approved by another developer.
Feature branch must be up to date.
Project must build.
Tests must pass.
